    "otherContributors": [
      "Jimmy Axelsson, Cambio Healthcare Systems",
      "Dennis Forslund, Cambio Healthcare Systems"
    ],
    "details": {
      "en": {
        "purpose": "This guide calculates urinary albumin:creatinine ratio (ACR).",
        "keywords": [],
        "use": "Use to calculate urinary albumin:creatinine ratio (measured in mg/g) from given values of urinary albumin (measured in mg/L) and urinary creatinine (measured in mg/L). Also for use to calculate albumin excretion rate (AER) which is approximately equal to the albumin:creatinine ratio, but with unit: mg/24hrs.\nTo obtain ACR in mg/mmol, divide ACR in mg/g by 10.\n\nFor use in concert with glomerular filtration rate (GFR) to stage and evaluate the risk of progression of chronic kidney disease (CKD).",
